author: stsp
msg: On the moves-scan-log branch, only show moves if the user actually chose 'f'.
(svn_cl__conflict_handler): Set show_moves in baton to TRUE if the user
chose find-move. Unset it again when moves were shown so that we don't
keep showing moves in case the user picks other options (such as 'h')
which cause the prompt to re-appear.

msg: Update to work with both Java 1.6 and 1.7. I think this looks like what has to be done to get wsimport and wsgen working from Maven for both java 1.6 and 1.7 - use the latest plugin from org.jvnet.jax-ws-commons, set thewsimport target to be 2.1, and include a dependency on the latest jaxws-tools
